A. Difficult to Determine Initial Values
The KF is based on recursive formulas (2) and (3) to iteratively calculate the system state. In order to ensure the accuracy of the KF, and must be set accurately. However, the initial value is usually set by experience or imagination, or assumes it is known, so as to avoid setting [25-27]. Therefore, it is necessary consider whether the size of initial values will affect the KF state in the LDS. If the initial value occurs deviation, will the difference between the KF state and the true state appear? Will the difference disappear rapidly?

